 Mean = m = E[X] = S [ x  ?  p(x) ] = 3.5 
Variance = s 2  = E[X 2 ] ? m 2  = S [ x 2  ?  p(x) ] - m 2  = 2.92 
 
Sampling Distribution of Samples' Mean (Xbar): Consider the case where two fair dice are rolled instead of one.

