Alternately, one may compute SSE by:
 
 
SSE = SS yy  ? m SS xy  = 54 ? (2.3)(23) = 54 - 52.9 = 1.1, 
 
 
as expected

 
Notice that this value of SSE agrees with the value directly computed from the above table.   The numerical value of SSE gives the estimate of variation of the errors s 2 :
  
 
  s 2  = SSE / (n -2) = 1.1 / (5 - 2) = 0.36667

 
 
 
The estimate the value of the error variance is a measure of variability of the y values about the estimated line. Clearly, we could also compute the estimated standard deviation s of the residuals by taking the square roots of the variance s 2 .
 
As the last step in the model building, the following Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) table is then constructed to assess the overall goodness-of-fit using the F-statistics:   
 
   
     
        
        Analysis of Variance Components
          
     
     
        
