     Suppose we apply the  t-test .  The statistic is  t = 3.207, with d.f. = 18.  The p-value is 0.003 indicating a very strong evidence against the null hypothesis. Now, by introducing a dummy variable x with two values, say 0 and 1, representing the two data sets,  respectively, we are able to apply  regression analysis :    
 
   
      
       
          
            
